                                    A Sudoku is a logical puzzle with a partially completed grid.
                                    The objective of is to fill a 9x9 grid with digits so that each column, each row, and each of the nine 3x3 squares, contains all of the digits from 1 to 9 only once.
                                    If the puzzle has been compiled correctly, there will be only one solution.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    Before you start solving classical versions of Sudoku, you can test if you understood the rules of the game with our Sudoku generator.
                                    The used version is slightly less complicated than the 9x9 version.
                                    You must fill the 6x6 grid in such a way that every row and column and each of the six 3x2 boxes, contains all the digits from 1 to 6 only once.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

